From 580579571d1f84e128b57d27e2a29f9924bbfbaa Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: =?UTF-8?q?Gr=C3=A9goire=20Layet?= <gregoire.layet@9elements.com>
Date: Thu, 18 Jun 2026 09:53:10 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] fan: improve find pwm-fan path
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

The PWM fans can't be detect by dbus-sensor if the device symlink file
name is not 'pwm-fanX'.

This file name is automatically generated by the kernel from the DTS
structure. The only way to have the file name to 'pwm-fanX' is to have
the pwm-fan nodes name 'pwm-fanX' as a child of the root node of the
DTS:

\`\`\`
/ {
    pwm-fan0 {
        compatible = "pwm-fan";
        pwms = <&pwm_tach 0 40000 0>;
    }
}
\`\`\`

This is an issue as the device tree should represent real hardware
structure. For example, on AST2600 devices, the fan PWM nodes should be
inside the pwm_tach parent node.

As described in the 'aspeed,ast2600-pwm-tach' binding example,

renamed the fan nodes to pwm-fanX to match dbus-sensors expectation.
the PWM fan nodes are patch of the controller:

\`\`\`
pwm_tach: pwm-tach-controller@1e610000 {
    compatible = "aspeed,ast2600-pwm-tach";
    reg = <0x1e610000 0x100>;
    clocks = <&syscon ASPEED_CLK_AHB>;
    resets = <&syscon ASPEED_RESET_PWM>;
    #pwm-cells = <3>;

    pwm-fan0 {
        compatible = "pwm-fan";
        tach-ch = /bits/ 8 <0x0>;
        pwms = <&pwm_tach 0 40000 0>;
    };

    pwm-fan1 {
        compatible = "pwm-fan";
        tach-ch = /bits/ 8 <0x1 0x2>;
        pwms = <&pwm_tach 1 40000 0>;
    };
};
\`\`\`

With the suggested device-tree, the symlink file name will end up as:
```
lrwxrwxrwx    1 root     root   0 Jun 15 11:50 device -> ../../../1e610000.pwm-tach-controller:pwm-fan0
```

This will not be matched by dbus-sensors.

As the kernel naming system will always put the node name at the end.
This patch fix the issue by comparing the end of the filename with
the 'pwm-fanX' string.

Tested:
- PWM and Tachometers sensors exist and appear in webui with pwm-fan
  nodes in root node (match old behavior)
- PWM and Tachometers sensors exist and appear in webui with pwm-fan
  nodes in pwm_tach node

Upstream-Status: Submitted [Gerrit, https://gerrit.openbmc.org/c/openbmc/dbus-sensors/+/91445]
Change-Id: Ib64edbedb93267d0a3a974cb29f1726c4226e4e8
Signed-off-by: Grégoire Layet <gregoire.layet@9elements.com>
---
 src/fan/FanMain.cpp | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/src/fan/FanMain.cpp b/src/fan/FanMain.cpp
index c6a8f57..4724c8d 100644
--- a/src/fan/FanMain.cpp
+++ b/src/fan/FanMain.cpp
@@ -167,7 +167,7 @@ bool findPwmfanPath(unsigned int configPwmfanIndex,
             continue;
         }
 
-        if (link.filename().string() == pwmfanDevName)
+        if (link.filename().string().ends_with(pwmfanDevName))
         {
             pwmPath = path;
             return true;
-- 
